title: Italian Baroque Painting (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
pdf / English / 1962 by Phaidon / 237 pages / 34.6 MB

A classic study, this serves both student and connoisseur as the standard introduction to Italian painting of the 17th century - from Caravaggio to Carlo Maratta. This concise and informative survey devotes separate chapters to the traditions and manifestations of Baroque painting. Written by Ellis Waterhouse, Baroque scholar and former Director of the Barber Institute of Fine Arts at the University of Birmingham, UK
